@startuml
title Dynamic Scalability Architecture - Horizontal Scaling Flow

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumers" as CSC
participant "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
participant "Cloud Service\nInstances" as CSI
participant "Resource\nReplication" as RR
participant "Virtual Server\nHost(s)" as VSH

CSC -> CSI : (1) send requests
ASL -> CSI : (2) monitor against\npredefined thresholds

== Workload Increases ==
CSC -> CSI : (3) request volume rises\n(workload exceeds thresholds)
ASL -> ASL : (4) evaluate scaling policy
ASL -> ASL : (5) initiate scaling\n(if eligible)
ASL -> RR : (6) signal replication
RR -> VSH : (7) create new\ncloud service instances
RR --> CSI : new instances added

== Steady State Resumes ==
ASL -> CSI : (8) resume monitoring\nand scaling

note over ASL
  The automated scaling listener is
  configured with workload thresholds and
  logic for how many additional IT
  resources can be provided per the
  consumer's provisioning contract.
end note

@enduml
